@oxtopus - I believe that having `nupic` be a namespace package is what is needed. `nupic.proto` is inside that namespace package but is not itself a namespace package.

Currently `nupic` is a namespace package and `nupic.bindings` is also one but only because @akhilaananthram had to put the nupic.core proto files into a sub-package of `nupic.bindings` during the nupic build. With this change, `nupic.bindings` will no longer be a namespace package.

